snippet.textDisplay: The national amthem is sung in pure Urdu which has Persian and Arabic influences in general as well. Most Pakistanis who are saying its not Urdu and too tough to grasp have not spoken pure Urdu probably in their lives and rely on the colloquial version of the language. Even as a young teenager, I understood the words because my Urdu is good. In fact, most people around me understand it perfectly. Please once and for all end this myth that the national anthem is in a foreign language it's those people who claim that who are unfamiliar with the Urdu language. Urdu has multiple loan words from Persian and Arabic but that doesn't make it Persian or Arabic just like English has mainly Latin and Greek influence but it remains a distinct language and isn't referred to as Latin or Greek.
